SIMPLE: demonstrative
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Demonstrative
<hw>De*mon"stra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧monstratif</ets>, L. <ets>demonstrativus</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the nature of demonstration; tending to
demonstrate; making evident; exhibiting clearly or conclusively.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Demonstrative</xex> figures.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An argument necessary and <qex>demonstrative</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Expressing, or apt to express, much; displaying
feeling or sentiment; <as>as, her nature was
<ex>demonstrative</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Consisting of eulogy or of invective.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Demonstrative</xex> eloquence.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Blair.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Demonstrative pronoun</b></col> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>, <cd>a
pronoun distinctly designating that to which it refers.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demonstrative</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Demonstrative
<hw>De*mon"stra*tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A
demonstrative pronoun; <as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧this⟦rdquo⟧ and ⟦ldquo⟧that⟦rdquo⟧
are <ex>demonstratives</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Demonstratively</ent>⟦br⟧
